body:
Avoid METH_O functions by default, since they do not match normal Python semantics.
Closes #3090.

commit.message: Change default of "always_allow_keywords" directive to True to avoid METH_O functions by default, since they do not match normal Python semantics.
Fix test after changing default of "always_allow_keywords" directive from False to True.
Make a doctest independent of the exact error message ("one argument" vs. "1 positional argument").

commit.message: Fix the direct calls to METH_O functions in the "cythonscope" test by disabling "always_allow_keywords" for the test scope module.
Fix unicode name handling of no-args functions when allowing keywords.
Fix warning output in unrelated test.
Fix a crash when a keyword argument is passed to a function that does not allow them. Previously, the reported key name was not set and thus NULL.
Fix some refcounting tests (apparently only in Py3.6) by restoring the original calling convention of their "get_refcount()" helper function.

Extend "always_allow_keywords" test to cover some edge cases.
Some are commented out as they currently only work with the fastcall implementation.

Goals:
 New version scheme: 3.x instead of 0.x.
 Change default `language_level` from `2` to `3`.
 Change default for `binding` directive from `False` to `True`.
 Fix some Python compatibility issues (if possible, allowing for breaking changes).

title: Change default of "always_allow_keywords" directive to True
